items.name: Elysium (2013) exoskeleton concept
items.description:
Elysium is a 2013 American dystopian science fiction action film written, produced, and directed by Neill Blomkamp. It was Blomkamp's second directorial effort. The film stars Matt Damon and Jodie Foster alongside Sharlto Copley, Alice Braga, Diego Luna, Wagner Moura, and William Fichtner.[4] The film takes place on both a ravaged Earth and a luxurious artificial world (Stanford torus design) called Elysium.[5] The film itself offers deliberate social commentary that explores political and sociological themes such as immigration, overpopulation, transhumanism, health care, worker exploitation, the justice system, technology, and social class issues.

You will mostly get a Matt Damon lookalike, but you can ask for a different gender, hair color, ...

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models or just buy me a coffee (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Exclusive models are also available on my Patreon.

Prompt : Elysium, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Elysium:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Elysium as trigger. Add woman and description if you want.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Elysium:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Elysium:0.8>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

You find yourself on the plane of Ixalan from Magic: The Gathering. You've decided to enjoy and immerse yourself in the culture of the Merfolk on Ixalan.

This LyCORIS was made to generate or make your characters into the merrow of Ixalan. Trained on 40 separate Ixalan Merfolk images I found through Google image search. Let's all be honest, other than not having a traditional merfolk tail, the Ixalan merfolk design is amazing.

To use the LyCORIS, just give it a basic description or just combine it with other LoRA and LyCORIS along with the trigger word. I tested it with a few and it looks like it works with other human character LoRAs quite well.

As you can see from the sample images provided, it's been tested on both realistic and anime models. Enjoy making some cool Ixalan merfolk. I'd love to see what people make with this being a big fan of Ixalan Merfolk myself.

items.name: RealCartoon-Realistic
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Updates:

9/13/23: Uploaded Version 8!

A branch off CheckPoint from RealCartoon3D

The Process:


This Checkpoint is a branch off from the RealCartoon3D checkpoint. This one's goal is to produce a more "realistic" look in the backgrounds and people. I am trying to avoid the more anime, cartoon, and "perfect" look in this model. It is a challenge that is for sure; but it gave a direction that RealCartoon3D was not really moving toward (as I wanted that one to just do what it is asked with a nice fun look). The process is the same as the base checkpoint (RealCartoon3D); but I look for more "real" merges. This (like the others) gets updates from RealCartoon3D as well. As with the base model, I try not to use checkpoints that are restricted on merges.

The Settings:

  • Width: 512 (normally would not adjust unless I flipped the height and width)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 1024, but 768 was my sweet spot)

  • Sampling Method: "Eular A" became pretty much the default as versions moved along, but "DPM++ SDE Karra" and "DPM++ 2M Karras" are favorites for me as well.

  • Sampling steps: 30-50 normally (30 being my starting point, but going up to 45 a lot of the time)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4k-UltraSharp most of the time), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (1.5 or 2 does well)

  • Clip Skip: 2

Would run ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but many times in the later versions I would not run this as it was not needed.

Why So Many Versions:

Because I wanted to share all the results that I felt reached a desired outcome. Allowed me to have fun, and I saw that many enjoyed them. Which motivated me to keep trying. Again, thank you.

Sugar painting is a traditional Chinese folk handicraft that involves creating pictures using sugar. As the name suggests, sugar painting is both a form of art and a sweet treat that can be enjoyed. It is also known as "sugar figurines," "sugar cakes," or "sugar lantern shadows" in Chinese folklore. There are two types of sugar painting: flat sugar painting and three-dimensional sugar painting.

Only a spoon and a shovel are used as tools for sugar painting. The sugar material used is usually a combination of red and white sugar with a small amount of malt sugar. It is heated on a stove until it becomes stringy and is then used to pour and mold shapes. The artist uses a small ladle to scoop up the melted sugar and quickly pours it onto a stone slab to create the desired shape. The skill of the artist's hands is crucial in creating the shape. Once the shape is complete, the sugar painting is lifted with a small spatula and attached to a bamboo skewer.

Sugar painting is an authentic folk art and a unique street market art that is loved by the people. It is a popular craft food that can be found at temple fairs, markets, and parks throughout China.

A request of @North_Bit8594962.

Priya Prakash Varrier is an Indian actress and social media personality, with over 8M followers on Instagram.

300-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (priyapvarrier:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Pseudo Flex (Base)
items.description:
Capabilities

  • Widescreen & portrait up to 1536x1024 and 1024x1536

    • 1920x1080 sometimes works, sometimes not. This is a limitation of pre-SDXL models' internal transformer architecture.

  • Photorealism - prompt with a year, a location, and a camera make.

  • Adventure - prompt coherence to allow silly requests.

  • Dark images - High guidance level with low CFG rescaling allows CRAZY dark images.

  • Bright images - Not bound to darkness like offset noise models, this terminal SNR prototype model is capable of producing pure white scenes.

  • Intentionally under-trained to allow additional fine-tuning.

  • Combine with textual inversions and see the true power of OpenCLIP!

No NSFW is trained into this model at all. It is family friendly.

Why it looks broken in Automatic1111?

Most of stable-diffusion-webui's samplers are unfortunately broken due to sampling from the leading timestep during inference. This is incongruent with the nature of training and inference in diffusion models:

  • During training, noise is added to a sample.

  • During inference, noise is removed from a sample.

When the noise addition ends during training, the instance is on the trailing timestep.

Most samplers start from the leading timestep, emulating a forward pass, rather than properly emulating the backwards pass.

Solution

  • Use DPM++ 2M sampler.

  • Install the A1111 extension for CFG (classifier-free guidance) rescaling

I find that higher CFG values around 7.5-9.5 produce stunning images, and a rescale of 0.0 allows the creation of very bright and very dark images.

However, if images appear over-contrasted or washed-out, you might need to up the CFG rescaling value to around 0.3 to 0.5. The maximum recommended value is 0.7, but this can result in washed-out images in a low-contrast manner.

Comparison vs 2.1-v and realism-engine:

Training details

This style LoRA closely replicates the style of characters drawn by artist Hiro Mashima, known best for the Fairy Tail and Rave Master series.

I find this LoRA usually works great standalone and exceptionally well used with other character LoRAs if you adjust the weight of the second LoRA to allow this one to shine through.

  • Hirez: ON

items.name: Laura Celia
items.description:
Laura Celia is a Dutch model and social media personality, with around 300K followers on Instagram.

250-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (l4uc3lia:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"
